This relation, as non-transitive, allows one to indicate the number of instances of c.

It is characterized by loss of maturation, nuclear hyperchromasia, high nuclear:cytoplasmic ratios, cytological and architectural atypia, and mitoses. Two morphological patterns have been described: basaloid (undifferentiated) and warty (condylomatous, bowenoid). It carries a significant but relatively low risk of progression to squamous cell carcinoma if untreated. (WHO 2020)
low grave vulvar squamous intraepithelial lesion; An intraepithelial lesion of the vulvar squamous epithelium associated with HPV infection. It is characterized by mild cytologic atypia.
low grade vaginal intraepithelial neoplasia; Vaginal intraepithelial neoplasia characterized by the presence of koilocytosis and disorganization and thickening of the basal layer.
